Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm slices, then chop into 2cm wide
chip shaped pieces (no need to peel!). Pop the chips on a low sided wide #baking tray{} in a single layer.
Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, @dried Italian herbs{1%tsp} and @smoked paprika{1%tsp} then season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out. Once your oven is hot, roast on the top shelf
of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> Use two #baking trays{} if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} then halve lengthways. Thinly slice widthways. Thinly
slice the @tomatoes{2%medium}, discarding the top. Pick the @mint{1}(leaves picked from stalks and
roughly chopped, discard stalks). Trim the @cucumber{1/2}, then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways
into small pieces. Quarter the @pomegranate{1}. Holding the pomegranate pieces over a #bowl{}
of water, scoop out the seeds into the bowl of water.

> Use a fork to do this, it helps to release the seeds.

Scoop out the seeds and set aside. Discard the white pith.

Pop the @panko breadcrumbs{10%tbsp} into a large #bowl{}. Add the @baharat spice mix{1%tsp} and
@water{2%tbsp} and mix together well. Add the @lamb mince{200%g} and, using your hands, mix until
very well combined. Form into kofta shapes (3 per person).

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands after handling raw meat!

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the koftas and fry
until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-12%minutes} in total. Carefully turn them
every 3 mins and lower the heat if they are burning.

> IMPORTANT: The koftas are cooked when they are no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, in a small bowl mix the @low fat natural yoghurt{75%g} and mint, season with salt and
pepper and set aside. Pop the @Greek style flatbreads{2} into your oven to warm through for
the last ~{3-4%minutes} of chip cooking time.

Layer each flat bread with the shredded gem, sliced tomatoes, cucumber, koftas, half the chips.
Drizzle with yoghurt and top with a sprinkle of pomegranate seeds. Serve any remaining chips on
the side with the yoghurt for dipping. Enjoy!